INSERT INTO "articles" ("id","slug","title","subtitle","author","published_at","read_time_minutes","image_url","seo_description","tags","content_html") VALUES(3,'the-humor-of-deedat','The Humor of Deedat','What if?','Haykal M. Zaidi','2026-03-07 16:02:14',1,'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/ahmed-deedat-_161129184959-817.jpg','Ahmad Deedat''s 1985 humor','Belief,Philosophy ','<p>This famous exchange between Ahmed Deedat and an atheist is a classic piece of religious rhetoric (often called a variation of Pascal’s Wager) that appears in several of his lectures and writings.</p>  <p>While Deedat used this logic throughout his career, the most famous recorded instance where he delivered this specific "humor" or retort was during his 1985 tour of the United Kingdom.</p>  <p>The Context of the Exchange The dialogue usually goes as follows:</p>  <p>Atheist: "How would you feel if you died and discovered that the Hereafter was a LIE?"</p>  <p>Ahmed Deedat: "Not worse than when you die and discover that the Hereafter is the TRUTH."</p>  <img src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/DwjbBg9X0AAFYVE.jpg" alt="Deedat_Pascal">  <p>Key Sources and Dates UK Tour (1985): Most researchers and video archives point to a Q&A session during his 1985 visit to the UK (specifically associated with the lecture series that included his famous appearances at the Royal Albert Hall). In many video titles, this specific segment is labeled as "Ahmed Deedat vs. An Atheist (1985)."</p>  <p>The Book "The Choice": Deedat included similar logic in his landmark book The Choice: Islam and Christianity (Volume 1/2), which was compiled and printed in its most popular form in April 1993.</p>');
INSERT INTO "articles" ("id","slug","title","subtitle","author","published_at","read_time_minutes","image_url","seo_description","tags","content_html") VALUES(6,'the-atheist-congratulation','Why Dr Zakir Naik Congratulates Atheists?','A simple look at his debate trick.','Haykal M. Zaidi','2026-03-07 18:13:26',2,'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/naik_1.jpg','Why does Dr. Zakir Naik congratulate atheists?','Belief,Philosophy,Science',replace('<p><b>The "First Half" of Faith</b></p>\n<p>When someone tells Dr. Zakir Naik they don’t believe in God, they usually expect a lecture. Instead, they get a "Congratulations."</p>\n\n<p>Why? Because of how the Islamic declaration of faith works. It starts with the words <strong>"There is no god..."</strong></p>\n\n<p>Naik’s logic is simple: most people are religious just because they were born into it. They follow whatever their parents told them. But an atheist has actually stopped to think. By saying "There is no god," the atheist has cleared away all the myths, idols, and superstitions.</p>\n\n<p><b>Clearing the Table</b></p>\n<p>Imagine you want to put a new tablecloth on a messy table. First, you have to clear off the old junk. To Naik, the atheist has already cleared the table. They’ve done the hard part of thinking for themselves and rejecting things that don''''t make sense to them.</p>\n\n<p>He often says: <em>"You’ve already agreed with the first half of my faith. Now I just have to show you the second half."</em></p>\n\n<p><b>The Bridge to Science</b></p>\n<p>Once he has the atheist listening, he doesn''''t use "holy books" as proof right away. Instead, he talks about the Big Bang, biology, and how the universe works. He tries to use <strong>logic and science</strong>—the very things atheists value—to prove that a Creator exists.</p>\n\n<p>Whether you agree with him or not, it’s a smart way to talk. Instead of starting a fight, he starts by finding the one thing they both agree on: that blindly following tradition isn''''t enough.</p>','\n',char(10)));
INSERT INTO "articles" ("id","slug","title","subtitle","author","published_at","read_time_minutes","image_url","seo_description","tags","content_html") VALUES(7,'the-worker-factory','You Were Trained Not to Think','From Rockefeller to the Prussian model—the truth about our "education."','Haykal M. Zaidi','2026-03-07 18:22:38',3,'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/the-prussian-school-all-power-to-the-canon-v0-8pjgi3piydr61.webp','An exploration of how the modern school system was designed to create workers, not thinkers.','Philosophy,Society,History','<p><b>The Factory Blueprint</b></p> <p>There is a famous quote often linked to John D. Rockefeller: <em>"I don’t want a nation of thinkers, I want a nation of workers."</em> Whether he said those exact words or not, the system he helped fund was built to do exactly that.</p>  <p>Our schools aren''t broken; they are doing exactly what they were designed to do. They are based on the <strong>Prussian model</strong>—an old system created to churn out obedient soldiers and disciplined factory workers who don''t ask questions and follow the bell.</p>  <p><b>The Meaningless Grind</b></p> <p>Think about your time in school. The endless note-taking, the high-pressure exams, the grades. In the real world, most of that info is useless. But the <em>habit</em> of doing boring, meaningless tasks for 8 hours a day? That is the real lesson. The system wants you to be "employable," which usually just means "compliant."</p>  <p><b>The Great Paradox</b></p> <p>Here is the uncomfortable truth: <strong>The world cannot function without workers.</strong> If everyone became a "disruptor" or a "philosopher" tomorrow, the power would go out, the food would stop moving, and society would collapse. We are stuck in a trap where we hate the machine, but we need the machine to survive.</p>  <p><b>Living in the "OS"</b></p> <p>The world is a bit of a mischief—a chaotic mess hidden behind a thin veil of order. Most people are as blind to this reality as a computer program is to its own code. We follow the "operating system" of society: Wake up, work, consume, sleep. We do it because the system has made us too tired to imagine anything else.</p>  <p>We accept the world as it is because we were trained to believe that a grade on a paper defines our worth. But once you see the code, it’s hard to go back to being just another cog.</p>');
INSERT INTO "articles" ("id","slug","title","subtitle","author","published_at","read_time_minutes","image_url","seo_description","tags","content_html") VALUES(8,'why-are-you-racist','Why are you racist?','We all are same','Haykal M. Zaidi','2026-03-07 19:37:40',2,'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/deedat_racism.png','Why are you racist - Ahmad Deedat','Society,Philosophy,Science',replace('  <video id="media-deedat" class="w-full rounded-xl shadow-lg mt-8 mb-4" controls playsinline>\n  <source src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/vid/deedat_racism_.mp4" type="video/mp4">\n</video>\n<div class="tuwa-subtitle-box" data-video="media-deedat" data-vtt="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/vtt/deedat_racism.vtt"></div> <p>You see Allah tells in the holy Quran  certainly Allah has created you all from a</p>  <p>male and a female and it is he who has made you  into nations and tribes that you may recognize</p>  <p>one another not that you may discriminate and  exploit one another. This is the most certainly</p>  <p>the noblest in the sight of God is he who is the  best in conduct. This is the standard laid out by</p>  <p>Allah, The Most High of judging not race, language, color or  riches but your behavior. the black and the white,</p>  <p>the rich and the poor, the African and the  Indian, the Arab and the Malay, everybody</p>  <p>rubbing shoulders using the same taps, using  the same towels, standing shoulder to-shoulder,</p>  <p>no gaps left between one individual and another  in our form of prayers between one devotey and</p>  <p>another so that the devil might get in between  you and your brother. The devil he was talking</p>  <p>about was your race. I''m white, he''s black. I''m  rich, he''s poor. that devil must not be allowed</p>  <p>to take to get in between you and him because  if you did they if I stand at a distance this</p>  <p>guy is a negro I''m an Indian I''m an Arab and  you end the salah they Assalamualaikum so peace</p>  <p>and blessings of Allah to everybody to the right  of me and I see here here is a man from Ethiopia</p>  <p>Assalamualaikum, I see here is a man from Africa. Assalamualaikum, next time I see  a man from China. Assalamualaikum, I said see a man from Timbuktu.</p>  <p>So, what He does is a system of eliminating racism</p>  <b><strong> This is an archived recording (cut) of Dr. Ahmad  Deedat''s speech entitled Racism and Blood Sacrifice  </strong> </b>','\n',char(10)));
INSERT INTO "articles" ("id","slug","title","subtitle","author","published_at","read_time_minutes","image_url","seo_description","tags","content_html") VALUES(9,'mansour-al-salmi-street-preaching','Mansour Al-Salmi','Street Preaching at a Youth Gathering','Haykal M. Zaidi','2026-03-07 20:12:01',15,'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/kl6Bh0co_HU-HD.jpg','Mansour Al-Salmi preaching during a youth gathering on the street in Saudi Arabia. ايات عذبه للشيخ منصور السالمي في جلسه ايمانيه رائعه .. جديد','Belief,Philosophy',replace('<iframe \n  id="media-salmi"\n  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/kl6Bh0co_HU?enablejsapi=1" \n  style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;" \n  frameborder="0" \n  allowfullscreen>\n</iframe>\n\n<div class="tuwa-subtitle-box" data-video="media-salmi" data-vtt="/vtt/salmi_2015.vtt"></div>\n\n<p><strong>Mansour Al-Salmi preaching during a youth gathering on the street in Saudi Arabia in 2015.</strong></p>','\n',char(10)));
INSERT INTO "articles" ("id","slug","title","subtitle","author","published_at","read_time_minutes","image_url","seo_description","tags","content_html") VALUES(10,'weapon-of-thought-narrative','Your Degree Won''t Save You','Why a PhD doesn''t cure idiocy, and how narrative builds invisible cages.','Haykal M. Zaidi','2026-03-07 20:43:45',5,'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/mind-cage.png','The difference between schooling and education, the illusion of intelligence, and why knowing how to think is your greatest weapon.','Society,Critical Thinking,Philosophy','<p>Let''s get one thing straight: having a PhD doesn''t mean you aren''t an absolute idiot. Mark Twain figured this out over a century ago when he warned us never to let our schooling interfere with our education. The distinction is everything. Schooling trains you on <em>what</em> to think so you can pass a test. True education is mastering <em>how</em> to think.</p> <img src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/twain-tweet.jpg" alt="Twain''s tweet"> <p>This isn''t just semantics; it''s survival. Humanity''s biggest weapon is not money. It is not wealth, status, or military might. Your absolute greatest weapon is knowing how to think correctly. If you surrender that, you are completely defenseless in the modern world.</p> <p>Look at how power actually operates today. They don''t need to use physical force to control you anymore. There is no boot on your neck. Instead, they control you with narrative. By strictly defining the borders of what is "reasonable" and what is "wrong," they build an invisible fence around your mind. If you step outside it, you aren''t dragged away by secret police—you are just socially exiled, labeled fringe, or canceled.</p> <p>And here is the most tragic, brilliant part of the whole setup: the authorities don''t even have to silence you. You silence yourself. You bite your tongue in meetings, online, and with your own friends because you don''t want to cross that invisible line. You trade away your greatest weapon—your own ability to reason—just to stay comfortable inside a cage someone else built.</p>');
INSERT INTO "articles" ("id","slug","title","subtitle","author","published_at","read_time_minutes","image_url","seo_description","tags","content_html") VALUES(11,'the-money-illusion','Your Money Isn''t Real','You check your banking app and feel rich. But what are those numbers, actually?','Haykal M. Zaidi','2026-03-08 00:10:41',5,'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/business-financial-concept-stack-money-background-flat-lay.jpg','Explore the truth about fiat currency, the end of the gold standard, and why the money in your bank account is just a collective illusion.','Economics,Finance,Philosophy,Society','<p>You open your banking app. The screen loads, and there it is: a healthy, commas-included number staring back at you. You let out a breath you didn''t know you were holding. You feel secure. You feel <em>rich</em>.</p>            <p>But let me burst that comfortable little bubble for a second: none of that is real.</p>            <p>We walk around treating the dollars, euros, or ringgit in our accounts like they are tangible laws of physics. We trade our time, our sweat, and sometimes our sanity for them. Yet, if you were to go to your bank tomorrow and demand the equivalent of that digital number in actual, physical gold, the teller would probably laugh—or quietly press the silent alarm.</p>            <img src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/grunge-style-bank-vault.jpg" alt="Stacks of Gold Bars in a Vault">            <p>It wasn''t always this way. Once upon a time, money was a receipt. A piece of paper was simply an IOU that you could swap for a shiny, heavy piece of metal sitting in a vault. The Gold Standard meant the paper in your pocket had intrinsic limits. But in 1971, that physical tie was severed completely.</p>                <img src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/OpenTuwa/OpenTuwaRe@main/img/1_uU7V5CrYYlpl3zeRMF_UfQ@2x.jpg" alt="President Nixon 1971">                  <p>Today, you are operating on a system called <strong>fiat</strong>. Fiat translates from Latin roughly to "let it be done" or "it shall be." Meaning, your money has value purely because a government <em>says</em> it does, and because everyone else collectively agrees to play along with the hallucination.</p>            <p>When a bank issues a mortgage or a loan, they don''t move physical gold from one room to another. They just type numbers into a database. Money is created out of thin air, backed by nothing but debt and the fragile promise that you will wake up tomorrow and keep believing in the system.</p>            <p>So, what is actual wealth? It''s not the currency. Currency is just the current flowing through the system—it is designed to lose purchasing power every single year thanks to inflation. Real wealth is the land, the businesses, the hard assets, the skills you hold, and the time you own.</p>            <p>The numbers on your screen? They are just a highly synchronized, globally accepted illusion. Play the game, but don''t forget the rules.</p>');
